ort List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def diagonalSum(self, mat: List[List[int]]) -> int:\n        n = len(mat)\n        primary_diagonal_sum = 0\n        secondary_diagonal_sum = 0\n        \n        for i in range(n):\n            primary_diagonal_sum += mat[i][i]\n            secondary_diagonal_sum += mat[i][n - 1 - i]\n        \n        # If the matrix has an odd dimension, subtract the middle element once as it's counted twice\n        if n % 2 == 1:\n            middle_element = mat[n // 2][n // 2]\n            return primary_diagonal_sum + secondary_diagonal_sum - middle_element\n        \n        return primary_diagonal_sum + secondary_diagonal_sum\n```\n\nThis solution calculates the sum of the primary and secondary diagonals of a square matrix. It handles the case where the matrix has an odd dimension by subtracting the middle element once, as it would otherwise be counted twice.", "estimated_date": 1598745600000}